description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Procurement Manager (Band 8A)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Arden &amp; Greater East Midlands Commissioning Support Unit (AGCSU) delivers high-quality commissioning support that is valued by our customers. Our services are built on a strong foundation of experienced people who build great relationships, a commitment to NHS values and a thorough understanding of our commissioners and the challenges they face. We provide real value to our customers by working at scale, creating the synergies and innovation that ultimately drive improved patient outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a new fixed 12-month term opportunity for 2 Procurement Managers (Band 8A) to work within our Clinical Procurement and Market Management team, (Advisory Services). The base is flexible and will be agreed prior to service commencement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;preferably be an experienced procurement professional and be a full member (or currently studying towards) of the Chartered Institute of Purchasing and Supply (MCIPS);&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;be based to be confirmed and will be required to work from home during the Covid pandemic and may be required to travel to customers to attend meetings as and when required after the pandemic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;work as part of a dynamic specialist Clinical Procurement and Market Management team within NHS Arden GEM Commissioning Support Unit (AGCSU). You will be responsible for specific procurement projects for clinical services that will support the AGCSU procurement team in delivering an effective and efficient service against the agreed work plan and key performance indicators for our customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full details are contained within the attached Job Description and Person Specification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The closing date for applications is 6th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note interviews will be held at via TEAMS call on 13th November2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name - Doug Hershaw&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title - Associate Director of Procurement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address - Doug.hershaw@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number - 07585 960611&lt;/p&gt;
